  "prompt": "How did Harry's get its name?",
  "response": "Harry's, a well-known brand of shaving and grooming products, was founded in 2013 by Harry's co-founders Jeff Raider and Andy Katz-Mayfield. The name \"Harry's\" is inspired by a personal connection\u2014it's derived from the name of one of the founders' grandfathers. This choice reflects a nostalgic and approachable branding approach, aiming to evoke a sense of tradition and authenticity in its products. The brand focuses on providing quality shaving supplies at an accessible price point, leveraging direct-to-consumer sales to eliminate middlemen.",
